      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it wasn't like a memory of the news... i hadn't even heard about the bridge yet. it felt more like the mug was showing me what was going to happen. like i was seeing the 'echo' of the event before it actually occurred. and it's not just once, it happens with other stuff too, usually with small things that seem totally random. if it's just a memory, why does it feel so much more like a premonition?",
